text: b'4/4 I took note of the President\xe2\x80\x99s decision to send Special Envoys to meet our authorities. I also thanked the President for facilitating the AU led negotiations on the GERD.'

b'3/4 The federal government is engaged in a law and order enforcement operation and the perpetrators of these atrocities will be brought to justice. We understand the concern of our friends and partners, especially the AU, because Ethiopia is their home.'

b'2/4 It has given me a good opportunity to brief the President on the genesis and objectives of the current operation, the attack on our defense forces, the atrocities and massacres committed and on the progress on the ground.'

b'1/4 I thank my brother President @cyrilramaphosa @AUChair2020 for his warm reception following our phone conversation last week and for the very fruitful discussion.\nI came to South Africa out of respect Ethiopia has for the continental organization and its current Chair.'

b'The #UNDay marks the 75th anniversary of the entry into force of the @UN Charter. Ethiopia, proud founding member, remains as always strongly committed to the principles enshrined in the Charter and to working for the world, starting from our region, to be a better place for all.'

b'Girls are promising agents of substantive change of the future. But this would require the provision of opportunities. We should not let Covid-19 deprive them of this potential. #DayOfTheGirl Bringing girls  #BackToSchool'
b'Congratulations to the brave women and men of @WFP under the leadership of David Beasley @WFPChief for winning the #NobelPeacePrize2020! A good recognition of their commitment and dedication.'

b'Je souhaite \xc3\xa0 tous nos amis/amies, partout o\xc3\xb9 ils se trouvent, et surtout ceux qui vivent parmi nous, dans leur deuxi\xc3\xa8me pays,l\xe2\x80\x99\xc3\x89thiopie, une f\xc3\xaate b\xc3\xa9nie de l\xe2\x80\x99 #aidelfitr .C\xe2\x80\x99est une unique opportunit\xc3\xa9 pour renforcer notre solidarit\xc3\xa9 face \xc3\xa0 nos d\xc3\xa9fis communs. #aidmubarak!'

b'I wish all our friends and specially those living with us in their second home, Ethiopia, a blessed #EidAlFitr. May it be an opportunity to strengthen our solidarity as we address our common challenges. #EidMubarak'

b'I insisted on the need to regenerate the mutual support mechanisms, networks on which women, particularly poor women, depend a lot to meet a variety of needs.  @UN_Women @OECD'

b'I also mentioned the in built assumption that little is enough when it comes to supporting women and that the most promising option is the provision of Universal social protection that includes the informal sector. This will benefit vulnerable populations, particularly women.'

b'In my contribution to the meeting on April 20 I insisted on the need for gender lens for the @covid19 response. Men &women experience crisis differently.The risk not only of remaining in the vicious circle but also of inter generational transfer of poverty has never been so real.'

b'Attended @UN_Women @OECD Women Leaders Roundtable on @covid19 & future.Pandemic will hit poor women hard by multiplying their many economic & social disandvantages. In #Africa  most women are in the survival sector of the informal economy that fetches minimal income.'
